HEADWORD: Kakaralli
<hw>Kak`a*ral"li</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of wood
common in Demerara, durable in salt water, because not subject to the
depredations of the sea worm and barnacle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

